The paper proposes a novel method for synthesizing person images in arbitrary poses, which involves utilizing pose information explicitly and training a U-Net-like generator in an adversarial way. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves generating images, which suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The paper also involves training a generator in an adversarial way, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves proposing a novel method, which suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
